   [edit]

                                      Name

   log - Record all user-interface input and output to a file.

   Status: Complete

   [edit]

                                    Synopsis

 log -Ae filename
 log -a  string
 log [-cdoq]

   [edit]

                                    Options

   +------------------------------------------------------------------------+
   |filename                     |Open filename and begin logging.          |
   |-----------------------------+------------------------------------------|
   |-c, --close, -o, --off, -d,  |Stop logging, close the file.             |
   |--disable                    |                                          |
   |-----------------------------+------------------------------------------|
   |-a, --add string             |Add the given string to the open log file.|
   |-----------------------------+------------------------------------------|
   |-q, --query                  |Returns open if logging is active or      |
   |                             |closedif logging is not active.           |
   |-----------------------------+------------------------------------------|
   |-A, --append, -e, --existing |Opens existing log file named filename and|
   |                             |logging is added at the end of the file.  |
   +------------------------------------------------------------------------+

   [edit]

                                  Description

   Invoked log with no arguments (or with -q) to query the current logging
   status. Pass a filename to start logging to that file (relative to the
   command line interface's home directory (see the home command)). Use the
   close option to stop logging.

   [edit]

                                    Examples

   To initiate logging and places the record in foo.log:

 log -new foo.log

   To append log data to an existing foo.log file:

 log -existing foo.log

   To terminate logging and closes the open log file:

 log -off


   [edit]

                                    See Also

   [edit]

                               Structured Output

   [edit]

On Success

 <result>
   <arg param="log_setting" type="boolean">setting</arg>
   <arg param="filename" type="string">log_filename</arg>
 </result>

   [edit]

Notes

     * setting is true (log file open) or false (closed).
     * log_filename is only included if the log is open.
     * currently prompts and input are not logged because "log" simply
       registers on the gSKI print callback. Need to implement fully.

   [edit]

                                  Error Values

   [edit]

During Parsing

   kUnrecognizedOption, kGetOptError, kTooFewArgs, kTooManyArgs,
   kInvalidOperation

   [edit]

During Execution

   kLogAlreadyOpen, kLogOpenFailure, kLogNotOpen, kInvalidOperation

